e-mail: promed@promedmail.org
[Although the probability that this is a Japanese encephalitis
epidemic is high, we have yet to see any confirmatory evidence
that this is the case. Fewer than 30 samples have been tested, &
only 16 of them had antibody to JE virus. If that is all the test
results there are, there has been no laboratory confirmation that
this is a JE epidemic, only presumptive evidence. When all is said
and done, the final tallies will go into health department reports and
chapter tables but will not be reliable. Such is the way of
international health statistics. - Mod.CHC]
